The paper deals with algorithms for computing the sparsest cut on directed graphs, which is a problem in graph theory and optimization. The use of cut-matching framework and max-flow computations suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The paper also involves game theory concepts, which may place it in the sub-category of cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper involves optimization and approximation algorithms, which may place it in the sub-category of cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
